            <title>[JDK-8309853] StructuredTaskScope.join description improvements</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8309853</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>StructuredTaskScope&amp;#39;s class description introduces join as waiting for all subtasks to finish but the join/joinUntil are phrased in terms of waiting for all threads to finish. The wording should be consistent.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
ShutdownOnXXX join inherit the description for join/joinUntil. It would better if they overrode the specification to make it clear that they wait until all subtasks finished or a subtask to succeed or fail.</description>
